<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-141] Documentation is lacking info about valid status levels</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-141</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/configuration.html#Configuration_with_XML&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/configuration.html#Configuration_with_XML&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;The level of internal Log4j events that should be logged to the console.&quot; should contain a list of all valid status levels.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same is the case further down the document at &lt;a href=&quot;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/configuration.html#StatusMessages&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/configuration.html#StatusMessages&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I understand that the StatusLogger is just a normal Logger so I assume that &quot;trace&quot;, &quot;debug&quot;, etc. are valid values - but I don&apos;t know and the documentation isn&apos;t telling me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A list of all valid values, preferably quite at the start of the configuration documentation, would help a lot. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
